# Citation And Replication

- Every item dossier should expose ranked citations.
- Preserve contradictory evidence instead of collapsing it away.
- Distinguish replication from practicality; they are related but not the same score.
- Penalize orphan tools, repeated caveats, retractions, and same-lab-only follow-up.
- When evidence is still being seeded, mark the gap explicitly.
